I stand before you today, as a self-represented defendant, to plead guilty to the charge of TV licence payment evasion. I am Lauren Dixon, 41 years old, and I accept full responsibility for my actions.

I want to emphasize that this offense was not committed with any malicious intent. It was a result of a genuine misunderstanding. I had erroneously believed that the bill for my TV licence had been taken care of. Regrettably, this misconception led to eight months of unlicensed use. However, as soon as I became aware of my mistake, I promptly rectified the situation by paying for a valid licence.

