I am fully prepared to take any necessary measures to rectify the harm caused and make this situation right. I am willing to cooperate with any remedial actions or programs that the court deems appropriate, whether it be through fines, community service, or further educational avenues, to demonstrate my commitment to addressing the consequences of my actions.

I do not wish for this statement to focus solely on remorse as I believe it is important for the court to understand the context of the offense. Nonetheless, I deeply regret the inconvenience and potential loss resulting from my oversight. I assure the court that this incident has served as a valuable lesson, one that I will carry with me moving forward.

In conclusion, I respectfully request the court's leniency and understanding in considering my mitigating factors. I plead guilty to the charge of TV licence payment evasion, acknowledging my responsibility and expressing my eagerness to make amends for any harm caused. Thank you for your attention and consideration.

Sincerely,
Lauren Dixon

