Your Honor,

I appear before you today as a self-represented defendant, ready to plead guilty to the charge of TV licence payment evasion. My name is Lauren Dixon and I am a 41-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. I take full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the seriousness of this offense.

First and foremost, I want to emphasize that my failure to pay the TV licence fee was not intentional. It was an unfortunate oversight on my part. I genuinely believed that the bill had been paid, and I was unaware of the unlicensed use for a period of 8 months. As soon as I realized my mistake, I promptly rectified the situation by paying for a valid license.

I have no previous criminal record, which I believe indicates that I am a responsible and law-abiding individual. I understand the gravity of this offense and the impact it has on society. I am truly sorry for any inconvenience caused by my unintentional violation.

Thank you for your time and attention.

Sincerely,
Lauren Dixon
